                            <comment id="13463503" author="xieliang007" created="Wed, 26 Sep 2012 04:15:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Mikhail, seems attached file is not for current community TRUNK version? since i saw :&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-style: solid;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeHeader panelHeader&quot; style=&quot;border-bottom-width: 1px;border-bottom-style: solid;&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;Hbase.thrift&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
 exception IOError {
   1: string message,
-  2: i64 backoffTimeMillis
+  2: i64 backoffTimeMillis,
+  3: string exceptionClass
 }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt; 

&lt;p&gt;there is no backoffTimeMillis parameter in struct IOError on current trunk code&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;and another thing, do we encourage using thrift2 more than thrift right now ? if that&apos;s right, maybe changing thrift2&apos;s TIOError is great ? &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
