                            <comment id="13463507" author="stack" created="Wed, 26 Sep 2012 04:26:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@Lang thrift2 tries to make the thrift apis more align w/ current trunk.  thrift1 has most usage and hence more trust.  What is lacking is an owner for either package.   Without this folks show up and fix their particular issue in whatever package they are using and then move on.  Would be grand if someone could drive thrift2 so it had all of thrift1 and was better aligned w/ the native apis.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13463511" author="xieliang007" created="Wed, 26 Sep 2012 04:36:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Got it, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=saint.ack%40gmail.com&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;saint.ack@gmail.com&quot;&gt;Stack&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
I&apos;d like to have a try&lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13463514" author="stack" created="Wed, 26 Sep 2012 04:44:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@liang That&apos;d be great. Would suggest first a survey of thrift1 and thrift2.  Figure what the difference is.  Do you want to have the two packages achieve parity?  Or do you want to add what is in thrift2 to thrift1 and keep up thrift1?  The exmamples package has stuff to exercise the thrift stuff.  A few more unit tests would probably not go amiss.  Good on you.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13463525" author="stack" created="Wed, 26 Sep 2012 05:10:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;@Liang ... or just pick up any outstanding thrift issues and take a look at resolving them?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13463532" author="xieliang007" created="Wed, 26 Sep 2012 05:20:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=saint.ack%40gmail.com&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;saint.ack@gmail.com&quot;&gt;Stack&lt;/a&gt; for nice guiding ! My plan is to resolve some outstanding thrift related issues firstly, afterwards i could know more details, then maybe i&apos;ll have a good feeling on how to fuse thrift&amp;amp;thrift2. Don&apos;t worry, i&apos;ll send a design note before making any big change&lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
